<p>In the latest development, Tetsuya Yamagami, 45, pleaded guilty at the opening of his trial in Nara to killing former prime minister Shinzo Abe with a homemade firearm during an election rally in July 2022 . Yamagami told police and the court he targeted Abe because of a grudge linked to the South Korea–founded Unification Church, which he blamed for his family&#x27;s financial ruin, and investigators have charged him with murder and violations of arms-control laws . The case has prompted renewed debate in Japan about politician security and potential reforms on donations and ties to religious groups while the legal process—including psychiatric examinations and court proceedings—continues in Nara District Court .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/frEV16as6H0eFLHphsNRQPRP-UcRsDWDyHdls3l4OkecSZvAYppG_FntnZD7f-iRd6Srp8LC-Z-5u5V-JnyOSMaqSbYicH4UxxrNQ-9R2sOE6F3zZYyZM5dIcfb6XuBM5Y2SaE0tx9Sfbz6fd7GXcAySWXBp0cV8qfGO4oHTAhNovg' alt='A vehicle believed to be carrying defendant Tetsuya Yamagami arrives at Nara District Court on the first day of his trial.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Defendant&#x27;s motive: Yamagami told investigators he blamed the Unification Church for his family&#x27;s financial collapse and said he targeted Abe because of the politician’s links to the group .</li><li>Court proceedings: The trial opened in Nara with Yamagami entering a guilty plea and the court scheduling psychiatric examinations as part of the legal process .</li><li>Security changes: The assassination prompted lawmaker security reviews across Japan and public debate about tightening protection at political events .</li><li>Weapon and charges: Prosecutors say the suspect used a homemade gun, and he faces murder charges plus alleged violations of Japan’s arms-control laws .</li></ul><blockquote>Everything is true - Tetsuya Yamagami</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Tetsuya Yamagami (defendant): He told police and the court he targeted Abe because of grievances tied to the Unification Church and his family&#x27;s financial ruin . (<a href='https://www.dw.com/en/japan-man-accused-of-killing-former-pm-shinzo-abe-pleads-guilty/a-74519503'>DW</a>)</li><li>Japanese prosecutors / justice system: Authorities have charged the defendant with murder and violations of arms-control laws and are conducting psychiatric examinations during trial proceedings in Nara District Court . (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/shinzo-abe-assassination-trial-in-japan-proceedings-against-yamagami/article70211304.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li><li>Public and political commentators: The attack renewed calls for tighter politician security and scrutiny of donations and ties between politicians and the Unification Church . (<a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/everything-is-true-shinzo-abes-killer-pleads-guilty-to-assassination-13945634.html'>Firstpost</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/shinzo-abe-assassination-trial-in-japan-proceedings-against-yamagami/article70211304.ece'>Shinzo Abe assassination case: Trial begins in Japan for man accused of using homemade firearm</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.abc.net.au/news/2025-10-28/japan-shinzo-abe-assassin-pleads-guilty-in-court/105944482'>Japan&#x27;s Shinzo Abe assassin pleads guilty in court</a> - abc.net.au</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/28/world/asia/japan-shinzo-abe-assassination-suspect-guilty.html'>Japanese Man Admits to Assassinating Former Prime Minister Shinzo Abe</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2025/10/28/gunman-pleads-guilty-to-murder-of-japan-s-ex-pm-as-trial-starts_6746845_4.html'>Gunman pleads guilty to murder of Japan&#x27;s ex-PM as trial starts</a> - lemonde.fr</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/everything-is-true-shinzo-abes-killer-pleads-guilty-to-assassination-13945634.html'>&#x27;Everything is true&#x27;: Shinzo Abe&#x27;